When a function is called in javascript. The function is pushed to call-stack. And picked up for execution. In case there is another function within that, The new function is pushed into the stack and its execution starts. Until it newer function execution is complete the first function remains in the stack. Once the second function is done it is popped and the control moves back to first.

Ex: 
func foo() { 
    console.log("Hi");
   bar();
   console.log("Bye"); 
} 
func bar() { 
   console.log("My name is Eve");
}
 Executions: 
Stack: foo() ----> Console ---> Hi 
Stack: foo(), bar() ----> Console ---> Hi, My Name is Ever 
Stack: foo() ----> Console ---> Hi, My Name is Ever, Bye

