The rendering and the JS evaluation is done on the same single thread in a JS Engine. 
When event loop is freed up, it run towards emptying the micro task queue first before leaping forward to other tasks or marcro job queues.

If the code has too many promises or has recursive micro tasks. The loop goes on, thus blocking the rendering. 
Ex: 
function foo() { 
  return new Promise((resolve) => { resolve(foo()); } 
}
